cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper primarily focuses on Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs) and their integration into the Internet of Things (IoT), which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper mentions security surveillance as one of the applications of WSNs, indicating that security is a concern in this domain. 

3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - WSNs are distributed systems, and the paper mentions scalability as one of the challenges faced by WSNs. 

4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes the use of Software Defined principles to improve QoS provisioning in WSNs, which involves control and management of the network. 

5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a software-based solution to improve QoS provisioning in WSNs, which falls under the domain of software engineering.
